  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Smallholder Commercialisation of Rice Farmers in Chinsali</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Chinsali District Rice Association is a membership driven association of rice farmers and traders registered in March 2009 with the registrer of Societies. CDRA current has 1, 250 members, 700 of which are male and 550 are female grouped in four zones, namely Central, Chambeshi, Kalela and Nashinga. The association is represented in these areas with the capacity to recruit and provide services to 2000 members 30% of whom are women. The organisation was formed to facilitate service provision to rice farmers. 

Chinsali District Rice Association (CDRA) will employ a private sector led market approach. This approach starts with the buyer (an identified local processing company called COMACO); CDRA will encourage farmers to produce what sells rather than the traditional method of producing and consequently identifying a potential market. Chinsali District Rice Association will sign a supply contract with COMACO to supply an agreed amount of Metric tonnes and it will in turn contract its members to produce and supply paddy through it. Developing this commercial supply chain system with COMACO does not only provide market for CDRA rice farmers, it also increases members access to reasonably priced inputs (such as seed, fertilizers, credit, extension services and technology) which COMACO agrees to provide and subsequently will result in increased incomes and sustainable rural livelihoods of the members.

The Overall objective: The overall objective is to increase the incomes, improve food security and reduce the vulnerability of small holder rice producers through enhancing their participation in the rice value chain (COMACO supply Chain).

Specific objectives:
(v)	To improve access to, and participation of Chinsali District Rice farmer association members in competitive markets through development of out-grower schemes;
(vi)	To facilitate rice farmers access to inputs including high quality seed, fertilizers and mechanization; 
(vii)	To facilitate increase in rice yields and improve quality of rice produced by  rice farmer associations members; 
(viii)	To set up a functional office for Chinsali District Rice Association with permanent staff to manage the day to day operations of the organization

Increase sales performance of Katerera ACE and organizational strengthening by means of improving financial management of the ACE and increase equity.</narrative>
  </description>
